The paper deals with the verification of quantitative information flow, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses complexity theory and formal definitions, which are topics in logic (cs.LO). Information theory (cs.IT) is also mentioned as a basis for the definitions. The paper deals with loop-free boolean programs, which are a topic in programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the self-composition technique, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
